    {\displaystyle A}
   is easily obtained.

The Pauli equation
Spacetime algebra allows the description of the Pauli particle in terms of a real theory in place of a matrix theory. The matrix theory description of the Pauli particle is:

  
    
      
        i
        ℏ
        
        
          ∂
          
            t
          
        
