          |
        
        ψ
        ⟩
        ,
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\hat {\gamma }}^{\mu }(\mathbf {j} \partial _{\mu }-e\mathbf {A} _{\mu })|\psi \rangle =m|\psi \rangle ,}
  where 
  
    
      
        
          
            
              γ
              ^
            
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\hat {\gamma }}}
   are the Dirac matrices. In the spacetime algebra, following Hestenes' derivation, the Dirac particle is described by the equation:

Here, 
  
    
      
