   is the spacetime vector derivative. This allows the same mathematical operator to describe the equations of motion for both electromagnetism and quantum mechanics, leading to a much simpler unification of the two.

Dirac spinors
The relativistic quantum wavefunction is sometimes expressed as a spinor field, i.e.

  
    
      
        ψ
        =
        
          e
          
            
              
                1
                2
              
            
            (
            μ
            +
            β
            i
            +
            ϕ
            )
          
        
        ,
      
    
    {\displaystyle \psi =e^{{\frac {1}{2}}(\mu +\beta i+\phi )},}
  where 
  
    
      
        ϕ
      
    
    {\displaystyle \phi }
   is a bivector, and

  
    
      
        ψ
        =
        R
        (
        ρ
        
          e
          
            i
            β
          
        
        
          )
          
            
              1
              2
            
          
        
