   can be directly corresponded with the components of a Dirac spinor, which can be easily checked by the fact that both have 8 scalar degrees of freedom.
This equation is interpreted as connecting spin with the imaginary pseudoscalar. 
  
    
      
        R
      
    
    {\displaystyle R}
   is viewed as a Lorentz rotation which a frame of vectors 
  
    
      
        
          γ
          
            μ
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \gamma _{\mu }}
   into another frame of vectors 
  
    
      
        
          e
          
            μ
          
        
      
    
